  "Astronomy and particle physics": "",
  "Marine biology, chemistry, geology, and oceanography": "",
  "Psychology and sociology only": "",
  "The Deepwater Horizon response required marine biologists to assess wildlife damage, chemists to understand oil dispersant behavior, geologists to evaluate the wellhead failure, and oceanographers to model oil plume movement through ocean currents.": "",
  "Which interdisciplinary approach was essential for understanding the cause and effects of the Flint, Michigan water crisis?": "",
