  "The Chernobyl disaster required nuclear physicists to understand the reactor failure, ecologists to study ecosystem contamination, epidemiologists to track radiation health effects, and atmospheric scientists to model the spread of the radioactive plume across Europe.": "",
  "What makes the study of the Amazon rainforest inherently interdisciplinary?": "",
  "It can be fully understood through geology alone": "",
  "It is located in only one country": "",
  "It only involves one type of organism": "",
  "It involves interactions among biology, hydrology, atmospheric science, soil science, and human geography": "",
  "The Amazon functions as an integrated system where biological diversity, hydrological cycling (the forest generates much of its own rainfall), carbon storage, soil nutrient cycling, and human land use are all interconnected, requiring multiple scientific disciplines to understand.": "",
  "Which case study demonstrated that acid rain required combining atmospheric chemistry and ecology to understand its full impact?": "",
  "The eruption of Mount Vesuvius, particularly regarding acid as typically measured in practice": "",
