  "Acid rain research in the 1970s-80s required atmospheric chemists to trace sulfur dioxide and nitrogen oxide emissions, and ecologists to document the impacts on lake ecosystems, forest health, and soil chemistry in Scandinavia and northeastern North America.": "",
  "The investigation of lead contamination in urban soils typically requires expertise from which fields?": "",
